íóŸRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2024-07-20-twin0256.mdŸ@ce262ff418c51f25b9cd9c5181ec05c5188825dfba95b29cefae9d06be7bdf4fπThis Week in Nushell #256ëßNushell⁄∂devyn 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13357] overhauled 
``$in``
 expressions
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13412] made 
``ast::Call::span()``
 and 
``arguments_span()``
 more robust
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13407] enabled plugins to find and call other commands
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13369] reported parse warnings and compile errors when running script files
WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13398] prohibited break/continue in the 
``each``
 and 
``items``
 commands
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13393] switched the positions of 
``<initial>``
 and 
``<closure>``
 in the 
``generate``
 command so that the closure can have default parameters
Zoybean 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13415] added a --quiet flag to the 
``watch``
 command
IanManske 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13401] refactored 
``window``
, 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13387] removed an unused field in 
``StateWorkingSet``
, and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13377] deprecated 
``group``
 in favor of 
``chunks``
132ikl 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13399] made the default config more consistent
jcgruenhage 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13384] switched from 
``dirs_next``
 2.0 to 
``dirs``
 5.0
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13382] used directories for autoloading
zhiburt 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13389] fixed an issue when column headers are printed on the table border
weirdan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13386] removed the 
``default``
 list-diving behavior
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13374] fixed a CI test failure on main (nu-json)
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/12907] added top-level crate documentation/READMEs
drmason13 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13352] updated the JSON format output to keep braces on the same line (issue #13326)
suimong 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/13408] made minor updates to the documentation of 
``reduce``
